                        MAIL commands

^Z: exit mail subsystem                  ?:  display help
>:  go to end of mail                    N:  put the latest UNIX news in your
<:  go to beginning of mail                  mail buffer
n:  next message                         U:  put the latest netnews in your
p:  previous message                         mail buffer
d:  delete message                       !:  execute UNIX command
u:  undelete message                     e:  edit mail buffer
r:  reply to message (^Y brings back     ^L: refresh screen
    text of old message)                 ^V: display next page of this message
s:  send message                         l:  go to next "Date" in newsletter
w:  write message to file
f:  forward message to another person 
P:  print current message                
 :  (space)     display next page of  
    current message                            
^H: (backspace) display previous page
    of current message
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       